    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against required level 3 due to single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol; this gap is accepted per regulatory guidance for Class II spinal implants. Uncertainty quantification performed via Monte Carlo methods; output uncertainty within acceptable bounds for all three QoIs. Overall credibility sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Package accepted at Medium assurance level.",
